@node introduction "Introduction"

@{b}Welcome to PlusEd !@{ub}

Now here is the ANSI editor that you've been waiting for !
Er, well... at first it was the ANSI editor that I have been waiting for.
I had just begun to write some ANSI texts for the PLUS BBS and I had already
tried several ANSI editors, but none of them was good enough for me. Some
used either IBM.font or Topaz.font, but not both, others did only have
25 lines for the text and again others were written in BASIC and terribly
slow, and some were...

OK, what I wanted to say was that there is just no really good ANSI editor
for the Amiga. And 'really good' means for me :

- Support for Topaz.font and IBM.font
- OS2.0 design
- Localized for OS2.1+
- Color requester
- Comfortable requesters
- Block manipulation funtions
- Writing in other directions than just from left to right
- Manipulating color and text separately
- Drawing lines and boxes with the mouse or keyboard
- High speed

So I decided to write my own ANSI editor, and because I am CoSysop of PLUS
BBS, I called it PlusEd. I implemented everything I needed and many more
things :

- Text length limited to 100 lines instead of 25 (1 screen)
- Support for Topaz and IBM font
- OS2.0 required, OS2.1 and OS3.0 supported
- OS2.0/3.0 design with GadTools gadgets & NewLook menus
- Localization; A german catalog is already included; I've also added the
  catalog sources just for the case that you'd like to create a catalog
  for your own language  (If you do so, please send it to me)
- Color presets for Amiga (OS2.0+), ANSI, EGA, DIEd, A2024; Ability to read
  your WB colors; Colors can be saved in your preferences
- Using @{"ReqTools.library" link reqtools} for nice requesters
- Navigation gadgets for writing in all directions
- Separate control of text and style/color
- Drawing lines and boxes (even overlapping ones) with the mouse or keyboard
- Quickwrite function with pre-made ANSI fonts
- Ability to create shadows, a nice 3D design and other amazing effects
- Recalculating IFF pictures into ANSI texts
- Written in highly optimized SAS/C code for maximum speed
...

After 9 months of development (including 4 months of beta-testing) PlusEd 1.00
was finally finished and I released it as Shareware. And now - after another 5
months - PlusEd 2.0 is finished ! Enjoy...

